### ImageObject Metadata

Source: https://context7.com/dariyd/react-native-document-scanner/llms.txt

Each scanned page is represented as an `ImageObject`. This object contains metadata such as URI, filename, MIME type, dimensions, file size, and an optional base64 encoded image string.

```APIDOC
## ImageObject Metadata

### Description
Each scanned page is represented as an `ImageObject` with comprehensive metadata and the processed image data.

### Interface
```typescript
interface ImageObject {
  uri: string;          // file:// URI in app cache
  fileName: string;     // UUID-based filename
  type: string;         // MIME type: "image/jpeg" or "image/png"
  width: number;        // pixels
  height: number;       // pixels
  fileSize: number;     // bytes
  base64?: string;      // optional base64 string
}
```

### Usage Example

#### Processing scanned images
```javascript
// Example: Processing scanned images
const result = await launchScanner({ quality: 0.8, includeBase64: false });

if (result.images) {
  for (const image of result.images) {
    console.log(`Processing ${image.fileName}`);
    console.log(`  Location: ${image.uri}`);
    console.log(`  Dimensions: ${image.width}x${image.height}`);
    console.log(`  Size: ${(image.fileSize / 1024).toFixed(2)} KB`);
    console.log(`  Format: ${image.type}`);

    // Copy to permanent storage
    const destPath = `${RNFS.DocumentDirectoryPath}/${image.fileName}`;
    await RNFS.copyFile(image.uri.replace('file://', ''), destPath);

    // Or upload directly from cache
    const formData = new FormData();
    formData.append('document', {
      uri: image.uri,
      type: image.type,
      name: image.fileName
    });
    await fetch('https://api.example.com/documents', {
      method: 'POST',
      body: formData
    });
  }
}
```

### ImageObject Fields

- **uri** (string) - The file URI pointing to the cached image file (e.g., `file:///...`).
- **fileName** (string) - The name of the image file, typically UUID-based.
- **type** (string) - The MIME type of the image, either `"image/jpeg"` or `"image/png"`.
- **width** (number) - The width of the image in pixels.
- **height** (number) - The height of the image in pixels.
- **fileSize** (number) - The size of the image file in bytes.
- **base64** (string) - Optional - The image data encoded as a Base64 string.
```

